				<wikidot:authorName>Ihp</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1267048</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoilers!</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>It's Linear B, yes. In fact, it's the name of one of the Olympians, written in Linear B&#8212; if you're having trouble figuring out which one, just add an H sound to the front.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13421401#post-4684222</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13421401/the-battle-of-baikal#post-4684222</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2020 05:31:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Percevale</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5980842</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm so excited to see more stuff about the 610 apocalypse! (And more content that's even tangentially HI related.) I like how easy it was to pick out who was with each of the involved GOIs, and how much distinct personality all the characters had even when they only had a couple lines of dialogue.</p> <p>Re: the name- It's Linear B, isn't it? As opposed to strictly Phonecian? Some friends and I came up with *Apaiteyo* as the closest transliteration but I imagine that isn't totally on point.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
